          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Trp195Glyfs*5) in the ARSA gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in ARSA are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 8962139, 10477432). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individual(s) with metachromatic leukodystrophy (PMID: 30674982). This variant is also known as c.576delC. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 1098313). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
